<br>
Well, Donnalinna has seen in her divinations that it is time.  It is time for her to be officially crowned, Crown Princess of Felwithe.  As such, she'd like to have a formal even to honor this unique experience.<br>
<br>
As such, Donnalinna needs aids.  She needs:<br>
<br>
- One clergyman to crown Donnalinna (I'd prefer a Tunare Holyman, but any cleric would do.<br>
- A Handmaiden to defend Donnalinna against any attacks or assassains.<br>
- Someone to give Donnalinna the Charge of Nobility<br>
- Someone to present Donnalinna to the court for her Trial of Office<br>
- An Honor Guard of at least 8 soldiers to protect the visiting dignitaries.  (They can be any class.)<br>
- Someone to act as Donnalinna's Prosecutor, to condemn her and question the act of coronation during the Trial of Office.<br>
- Someone to act as Donnalinna's Advocate, to counter the Prosecutor, and present why Donnalinna should be crowned for the Trial of Office.<br>
- Someone to decide upon Donnalinna's fate given the testimony of the Prosecutor and Advocate.<br>
- And lastly, should Donnalinna earn the crown, a troubador to sing stories of Donnalinna's triumph.<br>
<br>
Now, I would honestly like this to be a big guild event, and a big role-playing event.  I know most of our events aren't terribly formal, or even serious, but I would like this one to be.  At least, a bit more formal than most of our events.  A coronation is not something to be taken lightly.  And, as such, requires the utmost of devotion to whomever would like to help.  You are all invited, but I'd like only people who are seriously interetsed in a part to sign up for a part.  And, parts are first-come first served.<br>
<br>
Now, anyone can do a part.  So, for example, if Askyn wants to be the Advocate he can be.  If Templar Captain Varigon want's to be the Prosecutor he can be.  Etc., etc., etc.  I just ask that you be willing to role-play your part, and put some effort into it.  If you'd like to be a part, but want some help with lines, what to do, etc., sign up and we'll help you.  If we all put a bit of effort into this, it'll make it even more fun for everyone who can attend.<br>
<br>
Also, if you do sign up for a part, you might want to prepare a script for yourself, or some arguments as to why/why not Donnalinna should be crowned.  You've all read Donnalinna's diary entries up to this point, so you should all have some pretty good material to pull from.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I'd like to know if this might even be done, or it's it a pipe dream.  If enough of you are willing to attend, and willing to help, I think this might just be a blast.<br>
<br>
Oh, and I'll need someone to get a Ruby Crown, or some sort of tiara/crown to coronate me with.  (If it costs anything, I'll repay you.)<br>
<br>
So... anyone interested?<br>
<br>
